    <!-- Settings: Backup -->
    <string name="section_cloud_folder">Backup folder</string>
    <string name="cloud_caption">Pick a folder on this phone where trip CSVs and a settings backup will be saved</string>
    <string name="cloud_help_title">How to back up to OneDrive, Drive or Dropbox</string>
    <string name="cloud_help_body">Android\'s folder picker usually won\'t show OneDrive, Google Drive or Dropbox. Those apps don\'t expose a writable folder to other apps, so we save locally and let a sync app do the upload.\n\nSetup:\n1. Install Autosync (for OneDrive, Drive or Dropbox) or FolderSync from Play Store.\n2. In that app, sign in and create a sync pair: your chosen local folder → a cloud folder.\n3. Set it to \"Upload only\" with instant or on-change sync.\n4. Come back here and pick the same local folder.\n\nNew trips land in that folder when a recording ends. The sync app uploads them in the background.</string>
